Line 29. Subtract line 28 from line 16. This is your USVI adjusted gross income. Dollars.
Line 30.  Enter amount from Form 1040, line 61. Dollars.

Line 31. Enter the total of the amounts from Form 1040, lines 56, 57, 59a, 64a, 65, 66, and 71 (boxes c and d).  Include any uncollected social security and Medicare or tier 1 RRTA tax on excess golden parachute payments, or excise tax on insider stock compensation reported on line 60.  Also include any amount from Form 5329, Parts III, IV, V, VI, VII or VIII reported on Form 1040, line 58. Dollars.
Line 32.  Subtract line 31 from line 30.  Dollars.
Line 33. Enter amount from Form 1040, line 38. Dollars.
Line 34. Divide line 29 above by line 33. Enter the result as a decimal (rounded to at least 3 places). Do not enter more than 1.000.
Line 35. Multiply line 32 by line 34.  This is your tax allocated to the USVI. Dollars.
Line 36. Income tax withheld by the USVI. Dollars.
Line 37. 2013 estimated tax payments and amount applied from 2012 return. Dollars.
Line 38. Amount paid with Form 4868 (extension request). Dollars.
Line 39. Add lines 36 through 38. These are your total payments to the USVI.  Dollars.
Line 40.  Enter the smaller of line 35 or line 39.  Include this amount in the total of Form 1040, line 72.  On the dotted line next to line 72, enter "Form 8689" and show this amount.
Line 41.  Overpayment to the USVI.  If line 39 is more than 35, subtract line 35 from line 39. Dollars.
Line 42.  Amount of line 41 you want refunded to you. Dollars.
Line 43.  Amount of line 41 you want applied to your 2014 estimated tax. Dollars.
Line 44.  Amount you owe to the USVI.  If line 39 is less than line 35, subtract line 39 from line 35.  Dollars.

Line 45.  Enter the amount from line 44 that you will pay when you file your income tax return.  Include this amount in the total of Form 1040, line 72.  On the dotted line next to line 72, enter "Form 8689" and show this amount.
